<plot>John, a young, black, urban professional, is set off running from those determined to prevent him from getting where he needs to go. Those who oppose him seem well coordinated and funded, and so we are not sure he has a chance. However, when the film concludes, we see John wasn't running away from , so much as running to, something- something that is very important to each and every one of us. Opposition takes the notion of minority voting rights irregularities to its' logical and yet, extreme, limits.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?414865</url></doc>
